If running the application gives a "___ is damaged and can’t be opened" error, run this command at the .dmg file's directory:

xattr -cr ./@PROJECT_NAME@.dmg

or, if you've already installed it into /Applications:

xattr -cr /Applications/@PROJECT_NAME@.app

This happens due to macOS security (Gatekeeper) not allowing to run unsigned/unnotarized software, which applies to this application due to lack of development certification.